Two men were hurt in separate shootings in Brooklyn overnight, police said. At 3:50 a.m. Saturday, a 24-year-old man was shot  in the right hip on the 2200 block of Strauss Street, near Lott Avenue in Brownsville, police said. The victim told cops he “heard shots and felt pain.” EMS transported the man to Brookdale Hospital in stable condition, police said. Earlier, at 12:20 a.m., a 54-year-old man was shot in the right shoulder during a drive-by shooting in front of 460 E. 21st St. in Flatbush, authorities said. The victim, who was hit by gunfire from a dark sedan, was taken to Kings County Hospital with non-life-threatening injuries, cops said. “We don’t know if he was the intended target,” an NYPD spokesman said. There are no arrests.